    Description:
      "I. Accounting Area¹\n\n•\tMonthly closing package with the reconciliation of all balance sheet accounts;\n•\tAssessing monthly transactions to determine applicability for purposes of preparing tax filings under the Brazilian government regulatory authorities \n•\tBookkeeping of incoming and outgoing notes;\n•\tCalculation of taxes withheld at source;\n•\tMonthly Statements and Financial Statements of the Result;\n•\tPreparation of Annual Balance Sheet;\n•\tIncome Statements (Profit/Loss) – DRE²;\n•\tStatement of Changes in Equity (DMPL);\n•\tCash Flow Statement (DFC);\n•\tExplanatory notes;\n•\tAssembly of the financial statements and annual notes for auditing;\n•\tAssistance in sending documents and clarifications that are necessary for external accounting auditing;\n•\tManagement Representation Letter.\n\nII. Tax Calculation - Monthly³\n\n•\tMonthly calculation of taxes by the current tax regime;\n•\tIssuance of DARFs for payment of federal taxes;\n•\tIssuance of ISS guidance;\n•\tDelivery of withholding tax forms;\n•\tDelivery of the monthly tax returns;\n\nIII. Monthly Accessory Obligations\n\n• SPED EFD Contributions;\n• DCTF – Declaration of Federal Tax Credits;\n• DCTF Web – Labor and monthly tax obligation;\n• REINF – Monthly tax obligation;\n•\tSEFIP/GFIP – Collection and Information to Social Security;\n•\tE-Social – SPED.\n\nIV. Annual Accessory Obligations\n\n• DIRF – Withholding Income Tax Declaration (Annual);\n• SPED ECD – Digital Accounting Bookkeeping (Annual);\n• SPED ECF – Fiscal Accounting Bookkeeping (Annual);",
