    Service_TAG: "Business Formation",
    Taxas: null,
    Service_Onboarding:
      "Below are the steps involved in this process:\n\n1. Company Registration in the State: Registration and Certification of the Company with the State. The deadline varies according to each State, and can last from 15 days to 1+ month for completion.\n\n2. Registered Agent: It is necessary to appoint a registered agent at the time of company Registration. This step will run alongside the previous step.\n\n3. EIN - Employer Identification Number: The EIN is the equivalent to the CNPJ in Brazil. This step starts only after the completion of steps 1 and 2. If one of the partners has the Social Security Number (SSN, Equivalent to CPF in Brazil), the application process for the EIN with the IRS would take approximately 1 business day. * If they do not have the SSN, we will use the SSN of our partner as a third party and, in this case, the term would be up to 4 weeks with the IRS. *\n\n4. Operating Agreement or Bylaws: This is the company's corporate document, equivalent to the articles of association in Brazil, issued after its formation. This step starts only after the completion of steps 1 and 2. The document preparation process takes about 3 to 5 business days, with our Legal Department.\n\n5. Bank Reference: We will forward for your choosing, at the end of the process, references of Banks with which we have already worked whose experiences have been positive.\n--\nThe deadlines mentioned above start with:\n1. Payment related to the invoice related to the contracted service.\n\n2. Return of the Completed Incorporation Form, together with the documents required therein.",
    Individual_Item_ID: "2629712000010894150",
    State_Service: null,
    Assignment_Type: null,
    Package_Service: false,
    Created_By: {
      name: "Drummond Tech",
      id: "4978288000000328001",
      email: "tech@drummondadvisors.com",
    },
    Onboarding_PT:
      "Segue abaixo as Etapas envolvidas neste processo:\n\n1. Registro da Empresa no Estado: Registro e Certificação da Empresa junto ao Estado. O prazo varia de acordo com cada Estado, podendo durar de 15 dias a 1 mês para conclusão.\n\n2. Registered Agent: É necessário apontar um agente registrado no momento do Registro da empresa. Essa etapa irá correr junto à etapa anterior.\n\n3. EIN - Employer Identification Number: O EIN é o equivalente ao CNPJ no Brasil. Essa etapa inicia apenas após a finalização das etapas 1 e 2. Caso um dos sócios possua o Social Security Number (SSN, Equivalente ao CPF no Brasil), o processo de aplicação para o EIN junto ao IRS duraria cerca de 1 dia útil. Caso não possuam o SSN, utilizaremos o SSN de nosso sócio na condição de um terceiro e, nesse caso o prazo seria de até 4 semanas junto ao IRS.\n\n4. Operating Agreement ou Bylaws: Este é o documento societário da empresa, equivalente ao contrato social no Brasil, emitido após a Formação da mesma. Essa etapa inicia apenas após a finalização das etapas 1 e 2. O processo de Elaboração do documento dura cerca de 3 à 5 dias úteis, junto ao nosso Departamento Jurídico.\n\n5. Indicação de Bancos: Encaminharemos, ao final do processo, referências de Bancos com os quais já trabalhamos cujas experiências foram positivas.\n--\nOs prazos mencionados acima iniciam mediante:\n1. Pagamento referente a invoice relacionada ao serviço contratado.\n\n2. Devolução do Incorporation Form Preenchido, junto aos documentos requeridos nele.",
    Books_Accounting: "Business Formation",
    Books_Accounting_ID: "1858516000004910141",
    Description:
      "Business Formation Process in the following scopes State, Federal, and Corporate includes:\n\n•    Filing with the Department of the State;\n•    EIN - Employer Identification Number: application and issuance;\n•    Drafting of suggested Operating Agreement (LLC), Limited Partnership Agreement (LP), or Bylaws (CORP);\n•    Bank References for Bank Account Opening.",
